Hi Jeff,

Looks great! If you really want a lot of users, I would recommend=
 trying to
push a social news site. HackerNews is usually very amenable to =
these sorts
of posts, and it drives a lot of traffic. The last front-page I=
 had on HN
got 50 tweets and 5,000 unique visitors. Pretty easy to make it =
to the front
page too, just need 3 people to vote it up in the first 15 min=
utes of
submitting. Just be sure you've properly cached everything and can =
handle
the load, otherwise you will get DDoS'd pretty quick.

I'm happy to =
be one of those upvotes, just post a comments link to the list.
:)

Wesley
=
